(14, 2, 'content', 'Indonesia JCM Secretariat', '<p><strong>Indonesia&nbsp;Joint Crediting Mechanism (JCM) Secretariat&nbsp;</strong>was&nbsp;established by the Coordinating Ministry of Economic Affairs of the Republic of Indonesia in February 2014 to help manage the implementation of JCM activities between Indonesia and Japan. Its&nbsp;main function is to support the JCM Joint Committee and relevant stakeholders, to act as&nbsp;center of JCM information and communication, and to&nbsp;collaborate&nbsp;with all stakeholders to ensure the smooth implementation for the achievement of JCM purpose.&nbsp;The Indonesian secretariat is the only existing JCM Secretariat which serves the Government of Host Country. The Indonesia JCM Secretariat, based in Jakarta, works intensively with the JCM secretariat of the Japanese side in Tokyo.</p>\n\n<p>The Indonesia JCM Secretariat and the Japanese secretariat, as representatives of the JCM JC may jointly:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Prepare draft methodologies and draft rules and guidelines and submit&nbsp;them to the Joint Committee for its consideration, when necessary;</li>\n	<li>Receive new initiatives from candidate project participants;</li>\n	<li>Monitor the development of JCM related programs and implementation&nbsp;of JCM projects, taking into account sustainable development criteria and&nbsp;environmental integrity.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>And each secretariat may separately:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Develop environmental and sustainable development criteria for JCM&nbsp;implementation as well as identifying needs for capacity building, and&nbsp;submit them to the Joint Committee</li>\n	<li>Monitor the development of JCM Feasibility Studies activities</li>\n	<li>Facilitate the project participants to perform project-based capacity&nbsp;building</li>\n	<li>Establish and maintain a registry in line with the common specifications&nbsp;for registries, as developed by the Joint Committee</li>\n	<li>On the basis of notification for issuance of credits by the Joint Committee&nbsp;including for allocation of credits among project participants, issue the&nbsp;notified amount of credits to its registry.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>For general inquiries, the <strong>Indonesia JCM Secretariat</strong> can be contacted&nbsp;through email address: <a href=\"http://secretariat@jcmindonesia.com\">secretariat@jcmindonesia.com</a><br />\nThe Japanese JCM Secretariat can be contacted through email address:&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:id-jc-secretariat@jcm.go.jp\">id-jc-secretariat@jcm.go.jp</a></p>', '', 'navigation', 'active', 4, 'active', NULL, NULL, 'SysAdmin', '2018-11-08 22:32:32'),
(15, 2, 'content', 'Sectoral Scope', '<p>These sectors maybe developed under <strong>The Joint Crediting Mechanism</strong> (JCM)&nbsp;:</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Energy Industries (renewable/non-renewable sources);</li>\n	<li>Energy Distribution;</li>\n	<li>Energy Demand;</li>\n	<li>Manufacture Industries;</li>\n	<li>Chemical Industries;</li>\n	<li>Construction;</li>\n	<li>Transport;</li>\n	<li>Mining/Mineral Production;</li>\n	<li>Metal Production;</li>\n	<li>Fugitive emissions from fuel (solid,&nbsp;oil and&nbsp;gas);</li>\n	<li>Fugitive emissions from production and consumption of halocarbons and sulfur hexaflouride;</li>\n	<li>Solvent use;</li>\n	<li>Waste handling and disposal;</li>\n	<li>Reducing emissions from Deforestation and Forest Degradation in developing countries; and the role of conservation, sustainable management of forest and forest carbon stocks in developing countries (REDD-plus)</li>\n	<li>Agriculture.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://jcm.ekon.go.id/en/uploads/files/JCM scheme picture/03_Sectoral_Scope.PNG\" /></p>', '', 'navigation', 'active', 5, 'active', NULL, NULL, 'SysAdmin', '2016-03-13 03:15:44'),
(16, 3, 'content', 'JCM Project Cycle', '<p>Below figure describes the cycle to be followed by each JCM project:</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://jcm.ekon.go.id/en/uploads/files/JCM scheme picture/Skema_1.png\" /></p>\n\n<p>To understand more about the project participant role in the steps of project cycle, please download here : <strong><a href=\"http://http://jcm.ekon.go.id/en/uploads/files/Document JCM/Project Cycle/Project_Participants_Role_in_JCM_English.pdf\">project participant role_EN&nbsp;(PDF)&nbsp;</a>&nbsp;/ <a href=\"http://jcm.ekon.go.id/en/uploads/files/Document JCM/Project Cycle/Project_Participants_Role_in_JCM_BahasaIndonesia.pdf\">project participant role_ID (PDF)</a></strong></p>\n\n<p>To ensure the transparency of&nbsp;communication regarding the implementation of JCM project which have been conducted in Indonesia, Indonesian and Japanese side has developed the way of information sharing. Below is the document related to the way of information sharing :&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Download -</strong> <strong><a href=\"http://jcm.ekon.go.id/en/uploads/files/Document JCM/Project Cycle/revised_communication_way_for_SE_MOE_clean.pdf\">The way of information sharing of the JCM Model Projects and Leap-frog Projects</a></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Download - <a href=\"http://jcm.ekon.go.id/en/uploads/files/Document JCM/Project Cycle/revised_communication_way_for_SE_NEDO_clean.pdf\">The way of information sharing of the JCM Demonstration Projects</a></strong></p>', '', 'navigation', 'active', 1, 'active', NULL, NULL, 'SysAdmin', '2017-04-17 19:12:52'),
