(107, 73, NULL, 'Second Call for Proposal on City to City Collaboration Feasibility Study by MOEJ in JFY2017', '<p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"><strong>Ministry of the Environment Japan (MOEJ) is calling for second round of &quot;City to City Collaboration JCM Feasibility Study proposals for the Fiscal Year 2017</strong></p>\n\n<p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">This scheme encourages GHG emissions reduction activities on the city and regional scale and realizes a low carbon society by utilizing inter-city corporation between Japanese and Indonesian local government.Japanese local governments, research institutes, private companies and universities are co-operate and adjust the advanced low carbon technologies and systems to fit the local conditions to establish sustainable operation and maintenance systems in Indonesia. The agenda is set as follows:&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">Start call for request :&nbsp;<strong>July</strong><strong>-3, 2017</strong><br />\nDeadine for entities to submit their application : <strong>July-21, 2017</strong><br />\nAnnouncement of Selection : <strong>August-7, 2017</strong></p>\n\n<p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">Please also send project information using Project Idea Note format to&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:secretariat@jcmindoneisa.com\">secretariat@jcmindonesia.com</a>(please refer to :&nbsp;<a href=\"http://jcm.ekon.go.id/en/index.php/content/MzA%253D/propose_a_project\">jcm.ekon.go.id</a>).</p>', NULL, 'navigation', 'inactive', 6, 'inactive', 'SysAdmin', '2017-07-02 19:22:50', 'SysAdmin', '2019-04-07 19:48:49'),
(108, 29, NULL, '[CLOSED] Public Comment on proposed project PDD ID011 \"Reduction of Energy Consumption by Introducing an Energy-Efficient Waste Paper Processing System into a Packaging Paper Factory in Bekasi, West Java\" (July 22nd - August 20th, 2017)', '<p style=\"font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.8px;\">The draft&nbsp;PDD&nbsp;was submitted to the&nbsp;JCM&nbsp;secretariat between Indonesia and Japan on 21st July&nbsp;2017.<br />\nThe JCM secretariat of Indonesian and Japanese side makes the draft&nbsp;PDD&nbsp;publicly available for public comments in line with subsection 1.6.1. of the Joint Crediting Mechanism Project Cycle Procedure.</p>\n\n<p style=\"font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.8px;\">Information on the proposed project below is available for download.</p>\n\n<p style=\"font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.8px;\">All stakeholders are invited to provide their comments on the proposed project to the following both two email addresses&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:id-pdd-pi@jcm.go.jp; secretariat@jcmindonesia.com?subject=Public%20comment%20(Project)%20ID011&amp;body=Ref%20No.%3A%20ID011%0ATitle%3A%20Reduction%20of%20Energy%20Consumption%20by%20Introducing%20an%20Energy-Efficient%20Waste%20Paper%20Processing%20System%20into%20a%20Packaging%20Paper%20Factory%20in%20Bekasi%2C%20West%20Java%0AName%3A%20%0AAffiliated%20Organization%3A%20%0AE-mail%3A%20%0ACountry%3A%20%0APart%20of%20the%20document%20(A%2FB%2FC%2Fetc)%3A%20%0APage%20of%20the%20document%3A%20%0AComment%20on%20the%20page%3A%20\">id-pdd-pi@jcm.go.jp; secretariat@jcmindonesia.com</a>&nbsp;only in English, including the following information:<br />\n- Name:<br />\n- Affiliated Organization:<br />\n- E-mail:<br />\n- Country:<br />\n- Part of the document (A/B/C/etc):<br />\n- Page of the document:<br />\n- Comment on the page:</p>\n\n<p style=\"font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.8px;\">NOTE: The secretariat makes all received comments publicly available unless the&nbsp;TPE&nbsp;determines that the comment is unaut