(152, 73, NULL, 'Call for Proposal Model Project FY 2019 by MOEJ', '<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: 20.8px; font-family: Abel, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; text-align: justify; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Ministry of the Environment Japan (MOEJ) is calling for Model Project&nbsp;proposals for the Fiscal Year 2019</strong></p>\n\n<p>JCM is&nbsp;a bilateral&nbsp;cooperation between&nbsp;Government&nbsp;of Indonesia and&nbsp;Government&nbsp;of Japan to implement low carbon development activities in Indonesia through an incentive given by&nbsp;Government&nbsp;of Japan.&nbsp;JCM activities&nbsp;covers&nbsp;many sectoral&nbsp;scope, including energy efficiency, renewable energy, deforestation and forest degradation, waste management, fugitive emission, and manufacture industry.</p>\n\n<p>In order to support the implementation of candidate JCM projects, Ministry of the Environment, Japan (hereinafter referred to as &ldquo;MOEJ&rdquo;) has launched the &ldquo;JCM Model Projects (hereinafter referred to as &ldquo;model project&rdquo;),&rdquo; which includes collaboration with projects supported by the Global Environment Center Foundation (GEC)&nbsp;and other governmental-affiliated financial institution.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: 20.8px; font-family: Abel, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; text-align: justify; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">The schedule of the proposal submission is set as follows:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"background-color:Yellow;\"><strong>Friday, 5th April 2019</strong>: Call for proposals and relevant information will be announced on GEC&rsquo;s website</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"background-color:Yellow;\"><strong>Friday, 29th November 2019</strong>: Deadline for submitting </span><span style=\"background-color:Yellow;\">proposal</span><span style=\"background-color:Yellow;\">&nbsp;</span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><span style=\"background-color:Yellow;\">From 2019, GEC will accept proposals throughout the fore-mentioned period and preliminary selection of JCM Model Projects is done periodically while the budget is available.&nbsp;Thus, acceptance of proposals may close before the deadline due to the availability of the remaining budget.</span></p>\n\n<p>Candidates are encouraged to send proposal submission at the earliest time possible. The submission should&nbsp;be sent&nbsp;to:</p>\n\n<p><span style=\"background-color: yellow;\"><strong>Global Environment Centre Foundation Tokyo Office</strong></span></p>\n\n<p align=\"left\"><span style=\"background-color: yellow;\"><strong>4<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;Floor, Hongo Ozeki Bldg</strong></span></p>\n\n<p align=\"left\"><span style=\"background-color: yellow;\"><strong>3-19-4 Hongo, Bunkyo-ku, Tokyo 113-0033, Japan</strong></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">(GEC accepts proposals 10:00 - 12:00 and 13:00 - 17:00 (except Saturdays, Sundays and public holidays)</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Candidates</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A complete proposal must be&nbsp;submittes&nbsp;to GEC Tokyo Office in a sealed envelope by registered mail, private courier service or by hand-delivery. Proposal submitted by fax, e-mail or via&nbsp;internet&nbsp;will be rejected.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">More information on the guidelines for proposal submission can be downloaded&nbsp;<a href=\"http://jcm.ekon.go.id/en/uploads/files/Document JCM/Rules &amp; Guidelines - Forms/(tentative)2019_Guidelines_for_Submitting_Proposals.pdf\">here.</a></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Please refer to GEC website (<a href=\"http://gec.jp/jcm/kobo/mp190405/\">http://gec.jp/jcm/kobo/mp190405/</a>) for further information and application documents.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Abel, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">________________________________________</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: 20.8px; font-family: Abel, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; text-align: justify; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: 1.6em; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Please note that the JCM Model Project is the budgetary support from the government of Japan and it is our understanding that the projects selected for the Model Project are not a &ldquo;JCM project&rdquo; per se at the moment.&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Abel, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; text-align: justify; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The project participants of the selected Model Project need to go through the official JCM procedures including, for example, methodology development, validation&nbsp;and&nbsp;request for registration to the Joint Committee of JCM, where both&nbsp;side&nbsp;will discuss and consider all the matters relating to the implementation of the JCM.</p>\n\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Abel, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; text-align: justify; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">After these processes, the selected Model Project will be registered as the &ldquo;JCM project&rdquo; based on the decision of the Joint Committee.</p>\n\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: 20.8px; font-family: Abel, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; text-align: justify; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">_________________________________________</p>', NULL, 'navigation', 'active', 1, 'inactive', 'SysAdmin', '2019-04-07 19:47:34', 'SysAdmin', '2019-04-16 03:21:34'),
(153, 29, NULL, '[CLOSED] - Public Comment on proposed project PDD ID010 \"Energy saving through introduction of Regenerative Burners for aluminum holding furnaces of the automotive components manufacture in the Republic of Indonesia\"', '<p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">The draft&nbsp;PDD&nbsp;was submitted to the&nbsp;JCM&nbsp;secretariat between Indonesia and Japan on 08 April 2019.<br />\nThe JCM secretariat of Indonesian and Japanese side makes the draft&nbsp;PDD&nbsp;publicly available for public comments in line with subsection 1.6.1. of the Joint Crediting Mechanism Project Cycle Procedure.</p>\n\n<p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">Information on the proposed project below is available for download.</p>\n\n<p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">All stakeholders are invited to provide their comments on the proposed project to the following both two email addresses&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:id-pdd-pi@jcm.go.jp; secretariat@jcmindonesia.com?subject=Public%20comment%20(Project)%20ID013&amp;body=Ref%20No.%3A%20ID013%0ATitle%3A%20Power%20Generation%20by%20Waste%20Heat%20Recovery%20in%20the%20PT.%20Semen%20Indonesia%20(Persero)%20Tbk.%20factory%20in%20Tuban%0AName%3A%20%0AAffiliated%20Organization%3A%20%0AE-mail%3A%20%0ACountry%3A%20%0APart%20of%20the%20document%20(A%2FB%2FC%2Fetc)%3A%20%0APage%20of%20the%20document%3A%20%0AComment%20on%20the%20page%3A%20\">id-pdd-pi@jcm.go.jp; secretariat@jcmindonesia.com</a>&nbsp;only in English, including the following information:<br />\n- Name:<br />\n- Affiliated Organization:<br />\n- E-mail:<br />\n- Country:<br />\n- Part of the document (A/B/C/etc):<br />\n- Page of the document:<br />\n- Comment on the page:</p>\n\n<p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">NOTE: The secretariat makes all received comments publicly available unless the&nbsp;TPE&nbsp;determines that the comment is unauthentic in line with paragraph 42 of the Joint Crediting Mechanism Project Cycle Procedure.</p>\n\n<p style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\">This call for public com